:title("Java (subset) to LLVM IR compiler") ;
:description("Compiles a Java subset to an LLVM IR module and runs it with the built-in
IR interpreter and the MetaJS handle runtime (llvm.RunJS).

The subset: classes with fields (instance and static, with initializers), methods
(instance and static), constructors, single inheritance (class B extends A: inherited
fields and methods, overriding with dynamic dispatch, the implicit no argument super
constructor, and super.m() calls; a class must appear before its subclasses),
records with auto generated constructor and
accessors (a modern Java SE nod, like 'var' local declarations), object creation with
new, arrays (new int[n], new int[]{...}, a.length, indexing), the enhanced for loop
(for (var x : arr)), int / boolean / String / var / class types (types are parsed;
the semantics are dynamic), String concatenation with +, the String methods length(),
charAt(), equals(), substring(), indexOf() and isEmpty() (charAt yields a one char
String; there is no char type), System.out.println/print, System.exit, Math.abs/max/min,
if/else, while, do-while, both for forms, the classic colon switch on int or String
(fallthrough, stacked labels, default), break/continue, return, assignment (also
+= -= *= /= %=), postfix ++/--, the ternary operator, || && with short circuit,
== != < > <= >= (== compares objects by identity, use equals() for strings), + - * / %
(int arithmetic is 32 bit, / truncates) and unary - !.

Widened surface (parsed so a whole Java file is accepted): generics (<...>) and the
extra primitive keywords are parsed and dropped; casts ((Type) expr) are identity;
annotations (with or without arguments), implements/throws clauses and varargs (...)
are parsed and ignored. try/catch/finally + throw are accepted and, under
-warn-unsupported, the try block is still compiled and a throw still lowers its
expression (no exception model, so no unwinding). Interfaces, enums, annotation types,
nested/inner types, lambdas, method references and anonymous classes are accepted and
reported as not implemented; -warn-unsupported downgrades that to a warning so call
graphs / CFGs / traces still work on partly understood files.

Not genuinely modelled: the arrow switch, char/long/double literals, overloading,
implicit field access (fields are reached via this.x or ClassName.x - like the
explicit style many code bases enforce), real exception unwinding, functional
interfaces (so lambdas/method references are inert) and reflection.

Fields live directly on the instance object (js_get/js_set), methods become own IR
functions jsf_N(env, args) with the instance prepended to the arguments, stored on the
class descriptor object; calls dispatch through the js_mcall external. A constructor
always exists (a default one is generated) and first applies the field initializers.
The whole program becomes jsmain(env, args): it builds the class descriptors, then calls
Main.main. Self checking programs end with System.exit(failures).
The same language with the same semantics is interpreted directly by java-interpreter.abnf.") ;


// --- main rules

// Shared token productions (languages/lib).
:include("lib/cstyle-comments.abnf") ;
:include("lib/ident-dollar.abnf") ;
:include("lib/dq-strings.abnf") ;
:include("lib/numbers.abnf") ;
:include("lib/bools.abnf") ;

:startRule(Program) ;
:whitespace(Whitespace) ;

Program     <~~ buildMain(takeAll()) ~~>
            = [ Package ] { Import } { UnsupType | ClassDecl | RecordDecl } ;

// An optional package header (parsed and ignored) then repeated imports. Each
// import path is resolved against the runtime builtins (core.stdlibImports); one
// that does not resolve aborts the compile, unless -warn-imports downgrades it to
// a warning (see resolveImport in compile-core.js). 'import static a.b.C.d'
// resolves the dotted path too. QualName also accepts a trailing '.*' wildcard.
// Neither Package nor Import pushes a statement, so buildMain never sees them.
Package     <~~ pop() ~~> = KwPackage QualName ";" ;
Import      <~~ resolveImport(pop(), up.pos) ~~> = KwImport [ "static" KwEnd ] QualName ";" ;
QualName    <~~ push(stripWs(up.in)) ~~> = Id { "." Id } [ "." "*" ] ;

ClassDecl   <~~ push(makeClassStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ LeadMods ] KwClass Id <~~ push(up.in); curClassName = up.in ~~> [ SkipAngle ]
              [ KwExtends Id <~~ push({ext: up.in}) ~~> [ SkipAngle ] ]
              [ ImplementsSkip ] "{" { Member } "}" ;

// record Pair(int a, int b) { } -- generates fields, a constructor and accessors.
RecordDecl  <~~ push(makeRecordStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ LeadMods ] KwRecord Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ SkipAngle ] RParams
              [ ImplementsSkip ] "{" { Member } "}" ;
RParams     <~~ push({rparams: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ Type Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> { "," Type Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> } ] ")" ;

Member      = NestedType | Ctor | Method | Field ;

Ctor        <~~ push(makeCtor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ LeadMods ] [ SkipAngle ] Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ParamList [ Throws ] Block ;

Method      <~~ push(makeMethod(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Mods [ SkipAngle ] Type Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ParamList [ Throws ] Block ;

Field       <~~ push(makeField(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Mods FType Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "=" Expression ] ";" ;

// Modifiers before a member: annotations (with or without arguments) are parsed and
// ignored; ModWord keeps the modifier text so `static` is still detectable.
Mods        <~~ push({mods: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = { Annotation | ModWord } ;
ModWord     <~~ push(up.in) ~~>
            = ModKw ;
FType       <~~ push({ty: up.in}) ~~>
            = Type ;

// A parameter may carry annotations, `final` and varargs (`...`); all ignored.
ParamList   <~~ push({params: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "(" [ Param { "," Param } ] ")" ;
Param       = { Annotation | "final" KwEnd } Type [ "..." ] Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;

// Types are parsed and (apart from field defaults) ignored. Generic arguments
// (<...>), dotted names, extra array dimensions and the extra primitive keywords are
// accepted and dropped. Semantics stay dynamic.
Type        = ( PrimName KwEnd | "String" KwEnd | "void" KwEnd | "var" KwEnd
              | Id [ SkipAngle ] { "." Id [ SkipAngle ] } ) { "[" "]" } ;
PrimName    = "int" | "boolean" | "char" | "long" | "double" | "float" | "short" | "byte" ;

// Every statement production pushes exactly one thunk: function() -> undefined | signal.
Statement   <~~ push(stmtPos(pop())) ~~>
            = Block | If | While | Do | ForEach | For | Switch | Return | Break | Continue
            | Try | Throw | Assert | Synchronized | CtorCall | Labeled | Decl | Empty | ExprStmt ;

Block       <~~ push(makeBlockStmt(takeAll())) ~~>
            = "{" { Statement } "}" ;

If          <~~ push(makeIf(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwIf "(" Expression ")" Statement [ KwElse Statement ] ;

While       <~~ push(makeWhile(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwWhile "(" Expression ")" Statement ;

Do          <~~ push(makeDo(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwDo Statement KwWhile "(" Expression ")" ";" ;

// The classic colon switch (on int or String): execution starts at the first matching
// label and runs until a break or the end of the switch. Labels may stack.
Switch      <~~ push(makeSwitch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSwitch "(" Expression ")" "{" { SwitchCase } "}" ;
SwitchCase  = Case | Default ;
Case        <~~ push(makeCase(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwCase CondExpr ":" { Statement } ;
Default     <~~ push(makeDefault(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwDefault ":" { Statement } ;

// The enhanced for is tried first: its ':' fails fast for the classic form.
ForEach     <~~ push(makeForEach(pop(), pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" Type Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ":" Expression ")" Statement ;

For         <~~ push(makeFor(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwFor "(" [ ForInit ] ";" [ ForCond ] ";" [ ForPost ] ")" Statement ;
ForInit     <~~ push({k:"init", t:pop()}) ~~> = ForVar | ForExpr ;
ForVar      = DeclCore ;
ForExpr     <~~ push(exprToStmt(pop())) ~~> = Expression ;
ForCond     <~~ push({k:"cond", t:pop()}) ~~> = Expression ;
ForPost     <~~ push({k:"post", t:exprToStmt(pop())}) ~~> = Expression ;

Return      <~~ push(makeReturn(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwReturn [ Expression ] ";" ;

// break / continue accept an optional target label; a labeled form is recognized but
// not implemented (labels are dropped) and falls back to the plain innermost jump.
Break       <~~ push(makeBreakL(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>    = KwBreak [ LabelRef ] ";" ;
Continue    <~~ push(makeContinueL(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~> = KwContinue [ LabelRef ] ";" ;
LabelRef    <~~ push({label: up.in}) ~~> = Id ;

// assert cond [: message];  recognized, not implemented (no assertion model); the
// condition and the optional message are still lowered so their calls stay visible.
Assert      <~~ push(makeAssert(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwAssert Expression [ ":" Expression ] ";" ;
// synchronized (lock) { }: recognized, not implemented (no locks); the lock expression
// is lowered and the block still runs.
Synchronized <~~ push(makeSync(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwSync "(" Expression ")" Block ;
// label: stmt  recognized, not implemented (the label is dropped); the statement runs.
// NotSwitchKw keeps a switch's 'default:' / 'case ...:' from being misread as a label
// (Id matches keywords in this grammar), the same guard C's Label uses.
Labeled     <~~ push(makeLabeled(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = NotSwitchKw LabelName ":" Statement ;
LabelName   <~~ push({lbl: up.in}) ~~> = Id ;
NotSwitchKw = :script(~~
    (function() {
        var s = 0 // Whitespace is not skipped before a :script, so scan past it first.
        while (c.peek(s) === 32 || c.peek(s) === 9 || c.peek(s) === 10 || c.peek(s) === 13) { s++ }
        var kws = ["case", "default"]
        var hit = false
        for (var k = 0; k < kws.length; k++) {
            var w = kws[k]
            var ok = true
            for (var i = 0; i < w.length; i++) { if (c.peek(s + i) !== w.charCodeAt(i)) { ok = false } }
            if (ok) {
                var cc = c.peek(s + w.length)
                if (!((cc >= 48 && cc <= 57) || (cc >= 65 && cc <= 90) || cc === 95 || cc === 36 || (cc >= 97 && cc <= 122))) { hit = true }
            }
        }
        return hit ? abnf.newToken("\x01switch-label", 0) : undefined
    })()
~~) ;

// try/catch/finally and throw are implemented: throw calls js_throw, each try/catch/
// finally body compiles to its own closure handed to js_try, and a return/break/
// continue leaving a try or catch body becomes a control signal that excDispatch
// re-issues in the enclosing frame. The first catch clause wins (types, including
// multi-catch A | B, are parsed but not discriminated); a try-with-resources header
// is skipped.
Try         <~~ push(makeTry(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwTry [ SkipParen ] TryBody { CatchClause } [ FinallyClause ] ;
TryBody     <~~ push({trybody: pop()}) ~~>
            = Block ;
CatchClause <~~ push(makeCatch(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwCatch "(" CatchType Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ")" Block ;
FinallyClause <~~ push({finbody: pop()}) ~~>
            = KwFinally Block ;
Throw       <~~ push(makeThrow(pop())) ~~>
            = KwThrow Expression ";" ;

// An explicit constructor invocation (super(args) or this(args)): accepted and
// reported as not implemented (the implicit no-argument super already ran). The
// arguments are still lowered so their calls stay visible.
CtorCall    <~~ push(makeCtorCall(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = ( KwSuper | "this" KwEnd ) "(" [ Expression { "," Expression } ] ")" ";" ;

Decl        = DeclCore ";" ;
// A local declaration may carry annotations / `final` (e.g. @SuppressWarnings("x")
// int y = 1); LeadMods drops them (they do not change the lowering).
DeclCore    <~~ push(makeSeq(takeAll())) ~~>
            = [ LeadMods ] Type Declarator { "," Declarator } ;
Declarator  <~~ push(makeDecl(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ "=" Expression ] ;

Empty       <~~ push(function(b) { return b }) ~~>
            = ";" ;

ExprStmt    <~~ push(exprToStmt(pop())) ~~>
            = Expression ";" ;

// Every expression production pushes exactly one thunk: function() -> value.
Expression  = Assignment | CondExpr ;
Assignment  = KnownAssign | UnsupAssign ;
KnownAssign <~~ push(makeAssign(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "+=" | "-=" | "*=" | "/=" | "%=" | "=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Expression ;
// Compound bitwise / shift assignment (&= |= ^= <<= >>= >>>=): recognized, not
// implemented (no integer-bit externs); the right side is still lowered and stored,
// the operator is dropped. Tried after the known set, so plain '=' etc. are unaffected.
UnsupAssign <~~ push(makeUnsupAssign(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = Target ( "<<=" | ">>>=" | ">>=" | "&=" | "^=" | "|=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Expression ;

// An assignable place: a variable (this and class names are variables too),
// or a member/index path: this.x, p.x, Main.fails, arr[i].
Target      <~~ push(makeTargetRef(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> { "." Id <~~ push({key: up.in}) ~~> | TIndex } ;
TIndex      <~~ push({idx: pop()}) ~~>
            = "[" Expression "]" ;

CondExpr    <~~ push(makeCond(takeAll())) ~~>
            = OrExpr [ "?" Expression ":" Expression ] ;

OrExpr      <~~ push(makeOrAnd(takeAll(), true)) ~~>
            = AndExpr { "||" AndExpr } ;

AndExpr     <~~ push(makeOrAnd(takeAll(), false)) ~~>
            = BitOrExpr { "&&" BitOrExpr } ;

// The bitwise (| ^ &) and shift (<< >> >>>) levels are recognized but not implemented
// (there are no integer-bit externs); both operands are still lowered and one warning
// fires per operator run. A lone "|" that actually begins "||" fails its right side, the
// iteration rolls back, and the enclosing || level picks it up (same for "&" and "&&").
BitOrExpr   <~~ push(makeUnsupBin(takeAll(), up.pos, "bitwise operator")) ~~>
            = BitXorExpr { "|" BitXorExpr } ;
BitXorExpr  <~~ push(makeUnsupBin(takeAll(), up.pos, "bitwise operator")) ~~>
            = BitAndExpr { "^" BitAndExpr } ;
BitAndExpr  <~~ push(makeUnsupBin(takeAll(), up.pos, "bitwise operator")) ~~>
            = EqExpr { "&" EqExpr } ;

EqExpr      <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = RelExpr { ( "==" | "!=" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> RelExpr } ;

RelExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = InstOf { ( "<=" | ">=" | "<" | ">" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> InstOf } ;

// x instanceof Type [pattern]: recognized, not implemented (no type model); the operand
// is still lowered and the optional pattern variable is parsed and dropped.
InstOf      <~~ push(makeInstOf(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = ShiftExpr [ InstTail ] ;
InstTail    <~~ push({iof: 1}) ~~>
            = KwInstanceof Type [ Id ] ;

ShiftExpr   <~~ push(makeUnsupBin(takeAll(), up.pos, "shift operator")) ~~>
            = AddExpr { ( "<<" | ">>>" | ">>" ) AddExpr } ;

AddExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = MulExpr { ( "+" | "-" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> MulExpr } ;

MulExpr     <~~ push(foldBinary(takeAll())) ~~>
            = UnaryExpr { ( "*" | "/" | "%" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> UnaryExpr } ;

UnaryExpr   = Cast | PreIncDec | Neg | Not | BitNot | UPlus | PostfixExpr ;
// Prefix ++/-- yields the new value (genuine; reuses js_jadd/js_sub like the postfix
// form, so it must be tried before Neg so "--x" is not parsed as "-(-x)"). Unary + is
// identity. ~x is recognized but not implemented (no bit externs).
PreIncDec   <~~ push(makePreIncDec(pop(), pop())) ~~>
            = ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> Target ;
Neg         <~~ push(makeNeg(pop())) ~~>
            = "-" UnaryExpr ;
Not         <~~ push(makeNot(pop())) ~~>
            = "!" UnaryExpr ;
BitNot      <~~ push(makeBitNot(pop(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = "~" UnaryExpr ;
UPlus       <~~ push(makeUPlus(pop())) ~~>
            = "+" UnaryExpr ;

// A cast is lowered as identity ((Type) expr yields expr). A primitive cast accepts
// any unary operand; a reference cast excludes a leading '-'/'+' so `(a) - b` stays
// subtraction (Java's cast/subtraction disambiguation).
Cast        = PrimCast | RefCast ;
PrimCast    <~~ push(makeCast(pop())) ~~>
            = "(" PrimName KwEnd { "[" "]" } ")" UnaryExpr ;
RefCast     <~~ push(makeCast(pop())) ~~>
            = "(" RefType ")" UnaryNoPM ;
UnaryNoPM   = Not | PostfixExpr ;
RefType     = ( "String" KwEnd | Id [ SkipAngle ] { "." Id [ SkipAngle ] } ) { "[" "]" } ;

PostfixExpr = IncDec | NewExpr | SuperCall | CallMember ;
IncDec      <~~ push(makeIncDec(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Target ( "++" | "--" ) <~~ push(up.in) ~~> ;

// new Point(1, 2) | new int[]{1, 2, 3} | new int[n] | new Foo() { ... } (anonymous)
NewExpr     = NewAnon | NewObject | NewArrLit | NewArrSize ;
NewObject   <~~ push(makeNew(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwNew Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ SkipAngle ] "(" [ Expression { "," Expression } ] ")" ;
// An anonymous class: accepted, reported as not implemented; the constructor
// arguments still run so their calls stay visible under -warn-unsupported.
NewAnon     <~~ push(makeNewAnon(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = KwNew Id <~~ push(up.in) ~~> [ SkipAngle ] "(" [ Expression { "," Expression } ] ")" SkipBlock ;
NewArrLit   <~~ push(makeArray(takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwNew Type "{" [ Expression { "," Expression } ] "}" ;
NewArrSize  <~~ push(makeNewArray(pop())) ~~>
            = KwNew ( "int" KwEnd | "boolean" KwEnd | "String" KwEnd | Id ) "[" Expression "]" ;

// super.m(args): the method search starts at the superclass of the class the call
// appears in (curClassName is set while the class body is being built).
SuperCall   <~~ push(makeSuperCall(popName(), takeAll())) ~~>
            = KwSuper "." Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> "(" [ Expression { "," Expression } ] ")" ;

// A primary followed by method calls, field reads and indexing:
// System.out.println(x), p.dist(), this.x, arr[i], Main.check(...).
CallMember  <~~ push(foldCallMember(takeAll())) ~~>
            = Primary { MethodSfx | FieldSfx | IndexSfx } ;
MethodSfx   <~~ push({kind:"mcall", name: popName(), args: takeAll()}) ~~>
            = "." Id <~~ push({mname: up.in}) ~~> "(" [ Expression { "," Expression } ] ")" ;
FieldSfx    = "." Id <~~ push({kind:"field", name: up.in}) ~~> ;
IndexSfx    <~~ push({kind:"index", idx: pop()}) ~~>
            = "[" Expression "]" ;

Primary     = Lambda | MethodRef | "(" Expression ")" | TextBlock | DqString | CharLit
            | HexLit | BinLit | FloatLit | UscoreInt | SuffInt | IntLit | True | False | Null | VarRef ;

// Lambdas and method references are real closures on the handle runtime. A lambda
// captures the defining scope (js_closure); a functional-interface call site (any
// method call on the value, whatever the single abstract method is named) invokes
// it (js_call). The body is an expression (its value is the result) or a block (a
// return supplies the result).
Lambda      <~~ push(makeLambdaExpr(takeAll(), up.pos)) ~~>
            = LambdaHead "->" LambdaBody ;
LambdaHead  = "(" [ LamParam { "," LamParam } ] ")" | LamId ;
// A parameter is an optional type then a name; the explicit "Type LamId | LamId"
// alternation lets an untyped "(x)" work despite the possessive optional (Type
// would otherwise greedily consume the sole identifier).
LamParam    = [ "final" KwEnd ] ( Type LamId | LamId ) ;
LamId       <~~ push({lparam: up.in}) ~~> = Id ;
LambdaBody  = LamBlock | LamExpr ;
LamBlock    <~~ push({lblock: pop()}) ~~> = Block ;
LamExpr     <~~ push({lexpr: pop()}) ~~> = Expression ;
// A method reference Recv::m becomes a closure that forwards its arguments to
// Recv.m(...). Constructor references (::new) stay not implemented.
MethodRef   <~~ push(makeMethodRef(stripWs(up.in), up.pos)) ~~>
            = Id { "." Id } "::" ( Id | KwNew ) ;

Null        <~~ push(makeConst(null)) ~~>  = "null" KwEnd ;

// 'this' and class names resolve like variables.
VarRef      <~~ push(makeVarRef(up.in)) ~~>
            = Id ;

// ----- Widened literals: char, text block, hex / binary / floating-point / underscored /
// suffixed numbers. Recognized, not implemented (the value model is 32-bit int + String,
// so char has no numeric value and the others no distinct type). Each matches a form that
// plain IntLit cannot, so ordinary decimal integers still reach IntLit untouched. -----

// A char literal 'c' (escapes included). Reuses the balanced SkipChar shape.
CharLit     <~~ push(notImplExpr("char literal", up.pos)) ~~> = SkipChar ;
// A text block """ ... """ ; the !'"""' lookahead lets single and double quotes appear
// inside without ending the block. Whitespace is disabled inside so newlines are content.
TextBlock   <~~ push(notImplExpr("text block", up.pos)) ~~>
            = '"""' :whitespace() { !'"""' TBItem } '"""' :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
TBItem      = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" | "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
// Hex / binary: the 0x / 0b prefix is distinctive, so these never shadow a decimal int.
HexLit      <~~ push(notImplExpr("hex literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = ( "0x" | "0X" ) :whitespace() HexDig { HexDig | "_" } [ NumSfx ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
BinLit      <~~ push(notImplExpr("binary literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = ( "0b" | "0B" ) :whitespace() BinDig { BinDig | "_" } [ NumSfx ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
// A fractional literal has a '.', so it is distinct from an integer (and from x.y access).
FloatLit    <~~ push(notImplExpr("floating-point literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Dig :whitespace() { Dig | "_" } "." { Dig | "_" } [ NumSfx ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
// A decimal digit run containing an underscore (a digit-grouping literal like 1_000_000).
UscoreInt   <~~ push(notImplExpr("underscored integer literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Dig :whitespace() { Dig } "_" { Dig | "_" } [ NumSfx ] :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
// A decimal digit run with an L / F / D suffix (like 100L, 2F, 5D).
SuffInt     <~~ push(notImplExpr("suffixed integer literal", up.pos)) ~~>
            = Dig :whitespace() { Dig } NumSfx :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
HexDig      = "0"..."9" | "a"..."f" | "A"..."F" ;
BinDig      = "0" | "1" ;
Dig         = "0"..."9" ;
NumSfx      = "L" | "l" | "F" | "f" | "D" | "d" ;

// ----- Widened surface: generics, annotations, exceptions, casts (see :description) -----

// Balanced skips let a construct be ACCEPTED without being understood. String and char
// literals are matched first so braces/brackets inside them are never miscounted. No
// tags: nothing is pushed, so the consuming production places its own placeholder.
SkipBlock   = "{" { SkipItem } "}" ;
SkipItem    = SkipStr | SkipChar | SkipBlock | SkipOther ;
SkipStr     = '"' :whitespace() { SkipStrEsc | SkipStrChar } '"' :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
SkipStrEsc  = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipStrChar = "\x00"..."\x21" | "\x23"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipChar    = "'" :whitespace() { SkipChEsc | SkipChChar } "'" :whitespace(Whitespace) ;
SkipChEsc   = "\\" "\x00"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipChChar  = "\x00"..."\x26" | "\x28"..."\x5b" | "\x5d"..."\U0010ffff" ;
SkipOther   = "\x00"..."\x21" | "\x23"..."\x26" | "\x28"..."\x7a" | "\x7c" | "\x7e"..."\U0010ffff" ;

// A balanced < ... > run (generic parameters / arguments), parsed and ignored.
SkipAngle   = "<" { SkipAngle | SkipAngleItem } ">" ;
SkipAngleItem = "\x00"..."\x3b" | "\x3d" | "\x3f"..."\U0010ffff" ;

// A balanced ( ... ) run (annotation arguments), parsed and ignored.
SkipParen   = "(" { SkipStr | SkipChar | SkipParen | SkipPOther } ")" ;
SkipPOther  = "\x00"..."\x21" | "\x23"..."\x26" | "\x2a"..."\U0010ffff" ;

// Annotations (with or without arguments), modifier keywords, and the implements /
// throws clauses are parsed and ignored. LeadMods drops everything (headers with no
// static to track). ModWord (used by Mods) keeps the modifier text.
Annotation  = "@" Id { "." Id } [ SkipParen ] ;
ModKw       = ( "public" | "private" | "protected" | "static" | "final" | "abstract"
              | "synchronized" | "native" | "transient" | "volatile" | "strictfp" ) KwEnd ;
LeadMods    = { Annotation | ModKw } ;
ImplementsSkip = KwImplements Type { "," Type } ;
Throws      = KwThrows Type { "," Type } ;
CatchType   = Type { "|" Type } ;

// Type declarations accepted structurally, then reported as not implemented (so a
// whole Java file parses; -warn-unsupported lets the rest compile). Bodies are skipped.
UnsupType   = AnnotationDecl | Interface | EnumDecl ;
AnnotationDecl <~~ push(notImplStmt("annotation type", up.pos)) ~~>
            = { ModKw } "@" KwInterface Id SkipBlock ;
Interface   <~~ push(notImplStmt("interface", up.pos)) ~~>
            = LeadMods KwInterface Id [ SkipAngle ] [ KwExtends Type { "," Type } ] SkipBlock ;
EnumDecl    <~~ push(notImplStmt("enum", up.pos)) ~~>
            = LeadMods KwEnum Id [ ImplementsSkip ] SkipBlock ;

// A type declared inside a class body (nested/inner): accepted, reported as not
// implemented; its members are not lowered. It fires notImpl and pushes nothing, so
// makeClassStmt simply skips it.
NestedType  <~~ notImpl("nested type", up.pos) ~~>
            = LeadMods NestedKw Id [ SkipAngle ] [ SkipParen ]
              [ KwExtends Type { "," Type } ] [ ImplementsSkip ] SkipBlock ;
NestedKw    = ( "class" | "interface" | "enum" | "record" ) KwEnd ;

KwClass     = "class" KwEnd ;
KwRecord    = "record" KwEnd ;
KwImplements = "implements" KwEnd ;
KwInterface = "interface" KwEnd ;
KwEnum      = "enum" KwEnd ;
KwThrows    = "throws" KwEnd ;
KwTry       = "try" KwEnd ;
KwCatch     = "catch" KwEnd ;
KwFinally   = "finally" KwEnd ;
KwThrow     = "throw" KwEnd ;
KwPackage   = "package" KwEnd ;
KwImport    = "import" KwEnd ;
KwIf        = "if" KwEnd ;
KwElse      = "else" KwEnd ;
KwWhile     = "while" KwEnd ;
KwDo        = "do" KwEnd ;
KwFor       = "for" KwEnd ;
KwReturn    = "return" KwEnd ;
KwBreak     = "break" KwEnd ;
KwContinue  = "continue" KwEnd ;
KwNew       = "new" KwEnd ;
KwExtends   = "extends" KwEnd ;
KwSuper     = "super" KwEnd ;
KwSwitch    = "switch" KwEnd ;
KwCase      = "case" KwEnd ;
KwDefault   = "default" KwEnd ;
KwInstanceof = "instanceof" KwEnd ;
KwAssert    = "assert" KwEnd ;
KwSync      = "synchronized" KwEnd ;

// ---


:startScript(~~

    // Shared emitter machinery (module, handle constants, externs, loopStack
    // protocol, expression/statement builders); see the `core` knobs below.
    include("lib/compile-core.js")

    var feCount = 0 // Names hidden foreach counters.

    // ----- Imports & errors -----
    function fail(msg) { println("java compiler error: " + msg); exit(1) }

    // Import roots the runtime already provides (System, Math, String methods, ...);
    // importing them is a no-op. Anything else is an external library we cannot
    // resolve. resolveImport / stripWs live in lib/compile-core.js.
    core.stdlibImports = ["java", "java.util", "java.io", "java.lang", "java.math", "java.time", "java.util.function", "javax"]

    // ----- Expression thunks: function(block) -> {b, v} -----

    function makeCond(items) {
        if (items.length == 1) return items[0]
        return function(b) {
            var r = items[0](b)
            var thenB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var elseB = curF.NewBlock("")
            var mergeB = curF.NewBlock("")
            r.b.NewCondBr(truthy(r.b, r.v), thenB, elseB)
            var rt = items[1](thenB)
            rt.b.NewBr(mergeB)
            var re = items[2](elseB)
            re.b.NewBr(mergeB)
            var phi = mergeB.NewPhi([llvm.ir.NewIncoming(rt.v, rt.b), llvm.ir.NewIncoming(re.v, re.b)])
            return {b: mergeB, v: phi}
        }
    }

    function emitRefPath(b, ref) {
        var o = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, ref.name)])
        for (var i = 0; i < ref.path.length - 1; i++) {
            var s = ref.path[i]
            if (s.key != undefined) {
                o = callExt(b, "js_get", [o, emitStr(b, s.key)])
            } else {
                var r = s.idx(b)
                b = r.b
                o = callExt(b, "js_get", [o, r.v])
            }
        }
        var last = ref.path[ref.path.length - 1]
        if (last.key != undefined) return {b: b, obj: o, key: emitStr(b, last.key)}
        var kr = last.idx(b)
        return {b: kr.b, obj: o, key: kr.v}
    }
    function makeAssign(items) {
        var ref = items[0]
        var op = items[1]
        var valT = items[2]
        return function(b) {
            var r = valT(b)
            b = r.b
            var v = r.v
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                var nameV = emitStr(b, ref.name)
                if (op != "=") {
                    var old = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, nameV])
                    v = emitBin(b, op, old, v)
                }
                callExt(b, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, nameV, v])
            } else {
                var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
                b = p.b
                if (op != "=") {
                    var oldM = callExt(b, "js_get", [p.obj, p.key])
                    v = emitBin(b, op, oldM, v)
                }
                callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: v}
        }
    }
    function makeIncDec(items) {
        var ref = items[0]
        var extName = (items[1] == "++") ? "js_jadd" : "js_sub"
        return function(b) {
            var oneV = emitNum(b, 1)
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                var nameV = emitStr(b, ref.name)
                var oldV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, nameV])
                callExt(b, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, nameV, intWrap(b, callExt(b, extName, [oldV, oneV]))])
                return {b: b, v: oldV}
            }
            var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
            b = p.b
            var oldM = callExt(b, "js_get", [p.obj, p.key])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, intWrap(b, callExt(b, extName, [oldM, oneV]))])
            return {b: b, v: oldM}
        }
    }
    // Prefix ++/-- : like makeIncDec but yields the NEW value (genuine, same externs).
    function makePreIncDec(ref, op) {
        var extName = (op == "++") ? "js_jadd" : "js_sub"
        return function(b) {
            var oneV = emitNum(b, 1)
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                var nameV = emitStr(b, ref.name)
                var oldV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, nameV])
                var nv = intWrap(b, callExt(b, extName, [oldV, oneV]))
                callExt(b, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, nameV, nv])
                return {b: b, v: nv}
            }
            var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
            b = p.b
            var oldM = callExt(b, "js_get", [p.obj, p.key])
            var nv2 = intWrap(b, callExt(b, extName, [oldM, oneV]))
            callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, nv2])
            return {b: b, v: nv2}
        }
    }
    // Unary + is identity. ~x is recognized, not implemented (no bit externs); its operand
    // is still lowered so its calls stay visible.
    function makeUPlus(inner) { return inner }
    function makeBitNot(inner, pos) {
        notImpl("bitwise not", pos)
        return function(b) { var r = inner(b); return {b: r.b, v: hUndef} }
    }
    // A bitwise / shift operator run: recognized, not implemented. When no operator is
    // present (a single operand) it is a transparent pass-through, so ordinary expressions
    // lower byte-for-byte as before. Otherwise every operand is still lowered.
    function makeUnsupBin(items, pos, label) {
        if (items.length == 1) return items[0]
        notImpl(label, pos)
        return function(b) {
            for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) { var r = items[i](b); b = r.b }
            return {b: b, v: hUndef}
        }
    }
    // x instanceof Type [pattern]: recognized, not implemented; the operand is still
    // lowered. A single item (no instanceof tail) is a transparent pass-through.
    function makeInstOf(items, pos) {
        if (items.length == 1) return items[0]
        notImpl("instanceof", pos)
        var operand = items[0]
        return function(b) { var r = operand(b); return {b: r.b, v: hUndef} }
    }
    // Compound bitwise / shift assignment (a &= b): recognized, not implemented; the right
    // side is lowered and stored, the operator is dropped.
    function makeUnsupAssign(items, pos) {
        notImpl("compound bitwise/shift assignment", pos)
        var ref = items[0]
        var valT = items[2]
        return function(b) {
            var r = valT(b)
            b = r.b
            if (ref.path.length == 0) {
                callExt(b, "js_scope_set", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, ref.name), r.v])
            } else {
                var p = emitRefPath(b, ref)
                b = p.b
                callExt(b, "js_set", [p.obj, p.key, r.v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: r.v}
        }
    }

    // new C(args): set __class, then run the constructor with [obj, args...].
    // super.m(args): resolved through js_supercall, starting at the superclass of the
    // class the call appears in (captured at build time).
    function makeSuperCall(name, argThunks) {
        var defName = curClassName
        return function(b) {
            var clsV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, defName)])
            var supV = callExt(b, "js_get", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__super")])
            var thisV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, "this")])
            var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            for (var i = 0; i < argThunks.length; i++) {
                var r = argThunks[i](b)
                b = r.b
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, r.v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_supercall", [supV, thisV, emitStr(b, name), argsV])}
        }
    }

    function makeNew(items) {
        var clsName = items[0]
        var args = items.slice(1)
        return function(b) {
            var clsV = callExt(b, "js_scope_get", [curScopeV, emitStr(b, clsName)])
            var objV = callExt(b, "js_obj_new", [])
            callExt(b, "js_set", [objV, emitStr(b, "__class"), clsV])
            var argsV = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, objV])
            for (var i = 0; i < args.length; i++) {
                var r = args[i](b)
                b = r.b
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [argsV, r.v])
            }
            var ctorV = callExt(b, "js_get", [clsV, emitStr(b, "__ctor")])
            callExt(b, "js_call", [ctorV, hUndef, argsV])
            return {b: b, v: objV}
        }
    }
    function makeArray(items) {
        return function(b) {
            var arr = callExt(b, "js_arr_new", [])
            for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
                var r = items[i](b)
                b = r.b
                callExt(b, "js_arr_push", [arr, r.v])
            }
            return {b: b, v: arr}
        }
    }
    function makeNewArray(sizeT) {
        return function(b) {
            var r = sizeT(b)
            b = r.b
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_arr_new_n", [r.v, emitNum(b, 0)])}
        }
    }
    // An anonymous class is not lowered; evaluate the constructor arguments (so their
    // calls stay visible) and yield undefined.
    function makeNewAnon(items, pos) {
        notImpl("anonymous class", pos)
        var args = items.slice(1)
        return function(b) {
            for (var i = 0; i < args.length; i++) { var r = args[i](b); b = r.b }
            return {b: b, v: hUndef}
        }
    }
    // A cast is identity: (Type) expr lowers to expr.
    function makeCast(inner) { return inner }
    // A lambda is a real closure: its body becomes an own IR function jsf_N(env,
    // args) and the site yields js_closure(N, currentScope), so it captures the
    // defining scope. An expression body returns its value; a block body returns
    // via its return statement (or undefined when control falls through).
    function lamExprBody(exprBody) {
        return function(b) {
            var r = exprBody(b)
            r.b.NewRet(r.v)
            return deadBlock()
        }
    }
    function makeLambdaExpr(items, pos) {
        var params = []
        var exprBody = null
        var blockBody = null
        for (var i = 0; i < items.length; i++) {
            if (items[i].lparam != undefined) { params.push(items[i].lparam) }
            else if (items[i].lexpr != undefined) { exprBody = items[i].lexpr }
            else if (items[i].lblock != undefined) { blockBody = items[i].lblock }
        }
        var bodyStmt = blockBody != null ? blockBody : lamExprBody(exprBody)
        return function(b) {
            var idx = emitFunc(params, bodyStmt, false, null)
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(idx), curScopeV])}
        }
    }
    // A method reference Recv::m -> jsf_N(env, args) that resolves the receiver from
    // the captured scope and forwards the exact args array to js_mcall(recv, "m",
    // args). Static / bound / unbound all work (js_mcall picks the this-binding from
    // the receiver kind). ::new is not modelled.
    function makeMethodRef(text, pos) {
        var sep = text.indexOf("::")
        var tgtPath = text.slice(0, sep)
        var methodPart = text.slice(sep + 2)
        if (methodPart == "new") { return notImplExpr("constructor reference", pos) }
        var parts = splitDots(tgtPath)
        var bodyStmt = function(b) {
            var recv = callExt(b, core.scopeGetExt, [curScopeV, emitStr(b, parts[0])])
            for (var k = 1; k < parts.length; k++) {
                recv = callExt(b, "js_get", [recv, emitStr(b, parts[k])])
            }
            var ret = callExt(b, "js_mcall", [recv, emitStr(b, methodPart), curF.Params[1]])
            b.NewRet(ret)
            return deadBlock()
        }
        return function(b) {
            var idx = emitFunc([], bodyStmt, false, null)
            return {b: b, v: callExt(b, "js_closure", [handle(idx), curScopeV])}
        }
    }
    // Splits a dotted path "a.b.c" into ["a", "b", "c"].
    function splitDots(s) {
        var parts = []
        var cur = ""
        for (var i = 0; i < s.length; i++) {
            var ch = s.charAt(i)
            if (ch == ".") { parts.push(cur); cur = "" }
            else { cur = cur + ch }
        }
        parts.push(cur)
        return parts
    }
